# LinkedIn Visual & Post Specs (2026)

This file defines the canonical specifications for generating LinkedIn-ready visual content.
It MUST be followed in addition to:
- design-system.mdc
- engineering-guardrails.mdc
- narrative-copy.mdc

If there is a conflict, prefer:
clarity > consistency > minimalism > platform correctness.

---

## 1. Supported LinkedIn Post Types

Only the following post types are allowed:

- carousel
- single-image
- video
- document

Do NOT invent new post types.

---

## 2. Canonical Export Sizes (Single Source of Truth)

### 2.1 Carousel (Primary format)

Carousel posts are uploaded to LinkedIn as **Documents (PDF)**.

Design EACH slide at one of the following sizes:

- **Square (default):** 1080 × 1080 px (1:1)
- **Portrait (mobile-first):** 1080 × 1350 px (4:5)

Rules:
- Use PNG for slide generation
- Compile slides into a single PDF for upload
- Max slides: 7
- Min slides: 5
- Text-first design
- One statement per slide

Do NOT exceed these limits.

---

### 2.2 Single Image Feed Post

Use for one-off insights or visual metaphors.

Canonical size:
- **Square:** 1200 × 1200 px (1:1)

Allowed fallback:
- 1080 × 1080 px

Rules:
- PNG preferred
- Minimal text (≤ 12 words)
- Image must stand alone without relying on caption

---

### 2.3 Video

Use sparingly.

Allowed sizes:
- 1080 × 1080 px (1:1)
- 1920 × 1080 px (16:9)

Rules:
- MP4 format
- Silent-first (captions required)
- Motion must communicate meaning (no decorative animation)

---

### 2.4 Documents (Non-carousel)

Used for long-form content (reports, frameworks).

Rules:
- PDF only
- Max file size: 100MB
- Aspect ratios allowed: 1:1, 4:5, 16:9

---

## 3. Global Design Constraints (Mandatory)

Applies to ALL LinkedIn assets.

### 3.1 Mobile-first
- Assume majority mobile consumption
- Text must be readable at phone width
- Avoid thin fonts and low contrast

### 3.2 Safe Zone
- Keep all critical text away from edges
- No important content in corners
- Assume LinkedIn may crop previews

### 3.3 Visual Restraint
- Prefer negative space over decoration
- No stock photography
- No decorative icons
- No visual noise

---

## 4. Narrative & Copy Constraints (LinkedIn-specific)

These rules extend narrative-copy.mdc.

Allowed:
- Declarative statements
- Systems thinking
- Cause → effect reasoning
- Calm, factual tone

Forbidden:
- Marketing language
- Emojis
- “Tips”, “Secrets”, “Tricks”
- Calls to action inside visuals
- Questions beyond an optional first slide hook

Captions may contain light CTAs.
Visuals must not.

---

## 5. Required Metadata (for coded posts)

Every LinkedIn asset MUST define:

- postId (stable identifier, shared with Notion)
- postType (carousel | single-image | video | document)
- aspectRatio (1:1 | 4:5 | 1.91:1 | 16:9)
- theme (light | dark)
- altText (LinkedIn accessibility)

---

## 6. Cursor Guardrails

Cursor MUST NOT:
- Generate unsupported sizes
- Introduce new aspect ratios
- Add logos unless explicitly requested
- Add emojis
- Add stock imagery
- Add marketing copy

Cursor SHOULD:
- Default to carousel format when content is multi-step
- Default to dark theme for analytical/system content
- Keep visuals publish-ready without manual resizing

---

## 7. Intent

This spec exists to:
- Ensure platform correctness
- Maintain visual consistency
- Enable regeneration and automation
- Treat LinkedIn as a distribution layer, not a design tool

End of file.
